**03** **申请规划概述Overview of Application Planning**

这一部分展示了规划导师与你沟通交流以后为你制定的申请意向专业方向、申请国家、申请形象、学术主线、个人特色副线。申请形象指的是你的申请材料希望给招生官展现你是怎样一个人，在一些可量化可直接对比的成绩成就奖项等硬件之外，还能体现你怎样的个性、品质、故事、特点、兴趣和热情，往往这些软性的东西更能让招生官对你印象深刻。学术主线是申请意向专业方向的展开和细化，个人特色副线则是在学术主线之外你的第二主要特点，有可能是另一个有一定联系或一定反差的学术线，也有可能是非学术的例如户外冒险、艺术音乐、某种理念追求、某个方面的社会关怀等等。学术主线和个人特色副线共同塑造一个更为立体、更为多元、更有区分度的申请形象，使你从同专业方向的申请者中脱颖而出。

这一部分记录了你9-12年级完整的在校成绩情况。在校成绩是招生官对你学术能力判断的基础指标，好的在校成绩是申请顶尖大学的基本门槛。另外在校选课应体现与申请意向专业方向相一致或相关联的学术兴趣。
这一部分记录了你已经取得的各项标化考试成绩以及规划导师与你沟通交流以后一起制定的的未来标化考试计划。标化考试成绩是在校成绩之外的又一重要学术实力评判标准，顾名思义，它的意义在于更为标准化，不同学校的在校成绩往往很难比较，标化考试成绩弥补了这一点，于是也是很被招生官看重的。另外一些所在高中并不知名的学生可以通过标化考试进一步证明自己的学术能力基本面。

I Wharton On-Campus Leadership in the Business World

Intensive summer program for a select group of rising high school seniors who want an introduction to a top-notch undergraduate business education and the opportunity to hone their leadership, teamwork, and communication skills. LBW offers opportunities to learn about leadership in 21st century organizations through a dynamic and rigorous mix of classes with Wharton professors and business leaders, company site visits, and team-building activities. Admission to LBW is highly selective. Each year the admissions committee receives many more applications than there are available places. Wharton will select approximately 120students to attend per session. Selections are based on a record of academic excellence, demonstrated leadership, and a genuine interest in developing leadership skills.

This three week hands-on program is designed for students to research, brainstorm, prototype, and design a new to the world product through the lens of the Design Thinking process. Through this studio-based program, students will identify customer needs, generate product concepts, prototype, and design a physical product for showcase. Students will then work in teams around promising ideas to further develop and prototype the ideas into products as the keystone project for this course. In parallel, students will work on a series of individual prototyping skills building exercises and mini-projects to learn CAD design to utilize laser cutting and 3D printing services.

The Brown Environmental Leadership Lab (BELL) combines concepts in environmental studies, ecology, and leadership, with a mission of developing socially responsible leaders. At BELL, you' ll embark on a journey of learning and reflection while building community with the fellow student environmentalists in your program. 2025 Environmental Leadership Labs including Alaska, Eastern Sierras, Rhode Island, Florida Keys(NEW).

Leadership Seminars is a competitive, 10-day/ program on Notre Dame's campus for academically talented students who show impressive leadership within their communities. Notre Dame Leadership Seminars explore topics affecting the global commnunity. The courses are centered around vibrant discussion and a robust exchange of ideas. This creates a context in which students are encouraged to examine their own conclusions and hone their own leadership capacities by improving their communications and analytical skills. 2025 Courses including: Business-What Is It Good For? Global Issues-Violence and Peace in the Modern Age; The Environment-Science, Policy, Ethics; Inequality in America-America's Social and Economic Inequalities; The Power of Investing-Financial Literacy and the Miracle of Compound Interest.

This three week hands-on program is designed for students to research, brainstorm, prototype, and design a new to the world

needs, generate product concepts, prototype, and design a physical product for showcase. Students will then work in teams

impressive leadership within their communities. Notre Dame Leadership Seminars explore topics affecting the global commnunity.
